Description. Female (
Figs 1–7
). Idiosoma length 510 µm, width at level of coxae IV 560 µm, body margin straight posteriorly.

Dorsal idiosoma (
Figs 1–3
). Dorsum with single dorsal shield, surrounded by marginal shield, with line of fusion between shields; dorsal shield slightly hypertrichous, setae short, simple ( 26–33 µm) (
Fig. 1
). Marginal shield hypertrichous, setae short and needle-like ( 19–20 µm), or wide and robust ( 47–48 µm) (
Fig. 3
). Dorsal shield mostly smooth, excepting very fine reticulation near margins (
Figs 1–3
). Several sigilla present on anterolateral area of dorsal shield (
Fig. 2
). Surface of marginal shield covered by linear sculptural pattern.

Latigynal shields rectangular, with internal surface less expansive than external surface, the line between them differentiated by a thickened line of cuticle (long-dashed line in
Fig. 5
). Latigynal shields with smooth surface, each bearing 5–7 short ( 5–7 µm) smooth setae and an anteromedial group of pores, their mesal margins parallel. Mesogynal shield obscured but present, apparently fused to ventrianal shield. Internal genitalia not clearly visible (
Fig. 5
), but with weak vaginal sclerites meeting at a medial porose plate, from which two thick branches extend posteriorly.

Ventrianal shield with numerous short ( 8–9 µm), needle-like setae and its surface covered by reticulate sculptural pattern (
Fig. 6
). Anal valves with vestigial euanal setae. Peritrematal shield fused with exopodal, endopodal and metapodal region and with marginal shield at level of coxae II–III (
Fig. 4
). Peritremes almost straight, extending to level of coxae II, stigmata situated at level of anterior margin of coxae IV. Marginal shield with linear sculptural pattern and bearing short ( 9–10 µm), needle-like setae. Marginal shield deeply incised posteriorly but not forming separate plate (
Fig. 6
).

Male (
Figs 8–16
). Idiosoma length 470–480 µm, width at level coxae IV 490–500 µm, body straight posteriorly. Dorsal ornamentation and chaetotaxy same as in female.

Ventral idiosoma (
Figs 8–9
). Tritosternum same as female (
Fig. 9
). Sternal shield fragmented anteriorly, with paired presternal plates smooth and bearing needle-like setae
st 1
( 12–13 µm) and anteromedial sternal fragment smooth, subtriangular and without setae; sternoventral shield fused with endopodal shield and bearing seven pairs of smooth setae ( 9–10 µm) (
Fig. 8
). Genital shield linguliform, without setae, surface smooth, anteriorly with small round genital valve, basally fused to ventrianal shield, several sigilla present on basal area. Setation and ornamentation of ventrianal shield same as in female.
